<div id="review_1676641979" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1676641979" />
    <a title="Leslie Fisher" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25801961-leslie-fisher"><img alt="Leslie Fisher" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466298779p2/25801961.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1676641979?book_show_action=true">Jun 22, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Leslie Fisher" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Leslie Fisher" href="/user/show/25801961-leslie-fisher">Leslie Fisher</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/30735272-the-tainted-trust">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25801961-leslie-fisher?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25801961-leslie-fisher?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25801961-leslie-fisher?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1676641979" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2060866549480609665">This is the second book in the King Trilogy, and I enjoyed this one as much as the first. Though I read them in order, I think each book stands alone enough if you wanted to wanted to start in the middle of the series, but I am one who likes to read from the beginning to the end of the series, in order. I thought it was fun making connections between characters and situations in the two books. I listened to the Audible audio version and enjoyed the narrator, Matthias Lenssen, and all the unique </span>
  <span id="freeText2060866549480609665" style="display:none">This is the second book in the King Trilogy, and I enjoyed this one as much as the first. Though I read them in order, I think each book stands alone enough if you wanted to wanted to start in the middle of the series, but I am one who likes to read from the beginning to the end of the series, in order. I thought it was fun making connections between characters and situations in the two books. I listened to the Audible audio version and enjoyed the narrator, Matthias Lenssen, and all the unique voices he gives to the characters. This book is filled with interesting characters and interesting subjects. It keeps you on the edge of your seat. I'm definitely looking forward to the next book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2060866549480609665" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


